# King — production environment example
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy to `.env` and edit. Two ways to use it on the VPS:
#   • systemd:  ExecStart reads it via `EnvironmentFile=/srv/king/.env`
#   • shell:    `set -a; . ./.env; set +a; npm run server:prod`
#
# NOTE: the Node server reads process.env directly (no dotenv autoload), so the
# file only takes effect through systemd EnvironmentFile or an explicit export.
# Use plain KEY=value lines (no `export`, no quotes) for systemd compatibility.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Bind to localhost — the reverse proxy (Caddy/nginx) terminates TLS and
# forwards to this address on the same box.
HOST=127.0.0.1
PORT=3001

# Enables stricter startup warnings (e.g. warns if ALLOWED_ORIGINS is unset).
NODE_ENV=production

# Only your site's origin may open a WebSocket. Comma-separated for several.
# Replace <domain> with your real host, e.g. https://king.example.com
ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://<domain>

# Room persistence file. Put it on a persistent path; chmod 600 (sensitive:
# holds full hands + reconnect tokens). Set ROOM_STORAGE=memory to disable.
ROOM_STORAGE_FILE=.data/rooms.json

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DATABASE (OPTIONAL — ARCHITECTURE_DB_AUTH.md). Postgres is OFF by default:
# leave DATABASE_URL UNSET and the server runs exactly as the file/memory MVP.
# When set, /health additionally probes the DB (db: ok|error); without it
# /health reports db: disabled.
#
# To persist ROOMS in Postgres (Stage 2), set BOTH:
#   ROOM_STORAGE=pg
#   DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/king
# and run the migration ONCE first:  DATABASE_URL=… npm run db:migrate
# (ROOM_STORAGE=pg without DATABASE_URL fails fast with a clear error.)
#
# Rooms are stored as JSONB with game_type='king' (multi-game foundation).
# Stage 2 is rooms only — no accounts/auth/profile/stats yet.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ROOM_STORAGE=pg
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/king
# DATABASE_POOL_MAX=5

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AUTH / PROFILES (OPTIONAL — Stage 4, ARCHITECTURE_DB_AUTH.md §1.5/§5).
# The /api/* profile+settings surface and guest sessions are enabled ONLY when
# DATABASE_URL is set AND the migration has run (npm run db:migrate applies
# 0002_sessions_auth.sql). Without DATABASE_URL every /api/* route returns 503
# and play is unaffected.
#
# SESSION_SECRET: server-side pepper for hashing session tokens (and, later,
#   OAuth state). REQUIRED in production — a strong random string, e.g.
#   `openssl rand -hex 32`. Rotating it invalidates all existing sessions.
# COOKIE_SECURE: 'true'/'false' to force the Secure cookie flag. Default =
#   secure in production (NODE_ENV=production), insecure on dev http://localhost.
# SESSION_TTL_DAYS: session lifetime in days (default 30; clamped 1..365).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SESSION_SECRET=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
# COOKIE_SECURE=true
# SESSION_TTL_DAYS=30

# Dev-with-DB note: when the Vite client (http://localhost:5173) talks to this
# server on a different port, add its origin so credentialed /api fetches and the
# CSRF origin check pass:  ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:5173
# (Single-service prod — client served from this origin — needs nothing extra.)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GOOGLE OAUTH (OPTIONAL — staged; routes exist but return 503 until set up).
# When unset, /auth/google/* report disabled and the server never crashes.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=xxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=xxxx
# GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://<domain>/auth/google/callback

# Idle rooms with no connected players are deleted after this many hours;
# rooms with a connected player survive until the hard cap.
ROOM_TTL_HOURS=24
ROOM_HARD_TTL_HOURS=48

# Stage 7.2 — orphan rooms + disconnected substitute.
# An "orphan" room (no connected human — only bots and/or offline humans) is
# deleted after this many ms (lobby OR active game). Default 15 min.
ORPHAN_ROOM_TTL_MS=900000
# When a DISCONNECTED human's turn comes, wait this long (ms) before an AI
# substitute plays a legal move for them (the seat stays human + reconnectable).
# A room turn timer, if enabled AND shorter, takes precedence. Default 2 min.
DISCONNECTED_SUBSTITUTE_DELAY_MS=120000

# How long a completed trick stays on the table before the server auto-advances
# to the next trick (ms). Default 3000; clamped to [1000, 10000].
TRICK_ADVANCE_MS=3000

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CLIENT (build-time only — NOT read by the server). The client bakes this in
# at `npm run build`. Required for the path-based proxy below: without it an
# HTTPS page defaults to wss://<host> (root), which the proxy routes to static
# files, not the WS server. Set it to the proxied /ws path and rebuild:
#
#   VITE_WS_URL=wss://<domain>/ws npm run build
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VITE_WS_URL=wss://<domain>/ws

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VOICE CHAT ICE servers (OPTIONAL — Stage 25.5–25.6). Unset → STUN-only (works
# for most NATs; strict-NAT users fall back to text chat). To add a TURN relay,
# set a JSON array. Keep the TURN credential HERE (gitignored) — NEVER commit it.
# Malformed → STUN. Two ways (same JSON shape); see VOICE_CHAT_PLAN.md §7:
#
#   • VOICE_ICE_SERVERS       — SERVER runtime (preferred). Served at
#     GET /api/voice/ice-config; change + restart, NO client rebuild.
#   • VITE_VOICE_ICE_SERVERS  — CLIENT build-time fallback (baked into the bundle).
#
#   VOICE_ICE_SERVERS='[{"urls":"stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"},{"urls":"turn:turn.example.com:3478","username":"USER","credential":"SECRET"}]'
#   VITE_VOICE_ICE_SERVERS='[{"urls":"stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"},{"urls":"turn:turn.example.com:3478","username":"USER","credential":"SECRET"}]'
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# VOICE_ICE_SERVERS=
# VITE_VOICE_ICE_SERVERS=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RENDER (single Web Service) — see RENDER_DEPLOY.md / render.yaml.
# On Render set HOST=0.0.0.0 and DO NOT set PORT (Render injects it). Because
# the client is served from the same origin, it auto-connects to
# wss://<your-service>.onrender.com/ws — so VITE_WS_URL is OPTIONAL there.
# Example dashboard values:
#   NODE_ENV=production
#   HOST=0.0.0.0
#   ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://<your-service>.onrender.com
#   ROOM_TTL_HOURS=24
#   ROOM_HARD_TTL_HOURS=48
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
